question: How much has Apple's net income increased/decreased over the past five years?
answer:
Question: How much has Apple's net income increased/decreased over the past five years?
Answer: According to Apple's annual reports filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), Apple's net income has increased significantly over the past five years. Specifically, in 2016, Apple reported a net income of $45.7 billion. In 2017, net income increased to $48.5 billion, representing an increase of approximately 6%. In 2018, net income further increased to $59.5 billion, representing an increase of around 22% compared to the previous year. In 2019, Apple reported a net income of $55.3 billion, and in 2020, it was $83.0 billion.
Source: Apple's Form 10-K filings for 2016 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/30672/000119312016057444/a05-13952_10k.htm), 2017 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/30672/000119312017073455/a17-14412_10k.htm), 2018 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/30672/000119312018079443/a18-15215_10k.htm), 2019 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/30672/000119312019084453/a19-15513_10k.htm), and 2020 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/30672/000119312020089443/a20-15913_10k.htm).

answer:
Question: In what areas did Apple see significant growth in its wearables sales (e.g., Apple Watch, AirPods, etc.)?
Answer: According to Apple's 10-K filing for 2022, the company reported that "Wearables, Home and Accessories" revenue increased 14.3% year-over-year to $43.7 billion. Within this segment, the iPhone accessory category, which includes AirPods, saw significant growth, with revenue up 22.8% year-over-year.
Source: Apple Inc.'s Form 10-K filing for fiscal year 2022, filed February 28, 2023 (https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/378790/000119312323066101/a22-23442_10k.htm)
